10 war widows have been brought to Gallipoli by the Department of Veteran's Affairs for Anzac Day this Saturday . 
  They will be the guests of honour at the dawn service on the battlefields . 
  Many of the widows are visiting the battlefield for the first time . 
  Jean Pockett is the widow of a soldier who fought on the Western Front . 
  10,000 Australians and New Zealanders will attend the ANZAC Day commemoration . 
 